<br>
Personally I try to stay out of these 'my pet is better than yours' arguments, they give heartburn. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 329<br> <font color=#333333>(6/13/02 1:51:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=468.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: who is the pet king?</span><hr size=1>     Magicians are still the masters of pets, bar none.  Beastlords are a hybrid melee/shaman with rather powerful pets.  Just taking pets into consideration, and discounting the shaman-type spells and pet heals they have access to, magicians win the &quot;best pets&quot; argument without a doubt.  Further proof can be seen in that the Beastlord epic is a melee-type epic, whereas the magician epic is a spell that allows you to cast the baddest summoned pet any PC can muster. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uiwka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iwka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/02 11:36:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=468.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: who is the pet king?</span><hr size=1> Magicians, and this isn't because I love the class that I say this.  <br>
<br>
Yes, the BL pet is pretty cool, but beastlord warders do not have the versatility of a magician's pets.  We're the masters of summoning for a reason (and me being evocation is besides the point).  Different pets have different resists, different procs, each appropriate for different occasions, and while Beastlords can buff their pets and do some pretty spinky things, warders just don't have the range our pets do, if you see what I'm saying ... Yeah, I think it'd time for me to go get some food in me, I'm rambling  =P <p><br><img src="http://212.212.159.222/iwka/imagesP/iwkadom.gif"<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=187901">My Stuff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uquailin1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quailin1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(6/19/02 12:04:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=468.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: who is the pet king?</span><hr size=1> For this I would have to challenge a BL to a pet duel.<br>
<br>
I would say that if they can proc buff there pet we can ds ours). If We ds our  water pet it should eat right through thiers. I am not totally sure though. <br>
